div.span: Introduction to Algorithms and Programming II

div.class: ps_box-longedit psc_disabled psc_wrappable psc_has_value psc_nolabel psc_control-fullwidth psc_padding-1em psc_radius-1em psc_border-standard
div.span: This course is the continuation of COMP-1400 that introduces students to more advanced algorithm design and programming in a high level language such as C. The main objectives of the course are to develop the ability to identify, understand, and design solutions to a wide variety of problems. Topics covered include: multi-dimensional arrays, pointers, strings, advanced modular programming, records, binary files, recursion, stacks, linked lists and introduction to algorithm analysis. (Prerequisite: COMP-1000 (or MATH-1720) and COMP-1400.) (3 lecture and 1.5 laboratory hours a week).
